dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke run out (Pollock/Langeveldt) 92 (75b 7x4 4x6 103m) SR: 122.66

dismissalComment.html: Clarke is tragically run out, short of his century. He got to a three-figure mark , last in 2004-05 against Pakistan. The wait is not over yet. Symonds drives a full-pitched delivery to midwicket and stays rooted to the crease. Clarke runs down to the middle of the pitch and turns back. Too late. But what a fabulous knock it has been. Entertaining.

commentPostTextItems.html: The Australian players go into a huddle. Hands over each other's shoulder. They really wanted this one in the bag. Slowly.... they break away and walk towards the pavilion.

Three events halted the frenetic run-chase: Watson's throw to run out  de Villiers. Kallis walking in at no 3 and batting the way he did. Perhaps, Gibbs could have been promoted. And then Smith cramping up.  And Australia started hussling the batsmen. Pressure was intense, the required rate started rocketing and one by one, the batsmen went down.
This is Sriram Veera, signing off. Till tomorrow, adios.
